text: $1.40 for a kopi-O. Expensive.  Should just walk across 20m to the West Coast Hawker Centre to drink, just as good as and friendier staff.

Have you heard asking for extra cup with ice, charge 70 cents per cup?????? Just ice only with plastic disposable cup.  It is totally ridiculous, which authority can help to review the price for a Singaporean standard of living, can CASE assist on this matter?

The western food next to the Sze Cha is terrible. Order a pork rib and I get one big pieces of bone with inedible texture. I don’t stay there and too far to go back to complaint. Please do not patronise this western food stall. The only western food stall there. Huge disappointment.

Tried the dry prawn noodle..surprisingly quite good leh😊 $4.00
Yellow noodle, prawn x04, sliced pork and kangkong... very affordable! ++Plus point is the pork lard👍🏽 crispy!!!
Can eat lah..give it a try my friend👌🏽😄
The duck rice and noodle stall served good roasted duck. The Thai food stall is also nice.
